---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Macroline — Just say what you ate."
  description="The AI-native macro tracker. Describe a meal, scan a barcode, or connect Claude. Every food has a verified source."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-text">
      <p class="eyebrow">AI-native macro tracker</p>
      <h1>Just say what<br/>you ate.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Describe a meal, scan a barcode, or connect Claude. Every food has a
        verified source. No more guessing whether your tracker got the macros right.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a href="https://testflight.apple.com/join/SBhsGn9q" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-primary">
          Join TestFlight beta →
        </a>
        <a href="/features" class="btn-ghost">See features</a>
      </div>
      <p class="cta-sub">Public TestFlight open · App Store launch May 21 · Free tier with everything that matters · Pro $4.99/mo unlocks AI input + Claude</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Stylized in-app preview card — gives the hero a visual anchor.
         Hidden on ≤720px (v1.5): at narrow widths the inline food entries
         shrink below ~10px effective text size and become illegible — visual
         filler instead of product proof. The hero copy + CTAs own mobile. -->
    <div class="hero-preview" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="card-stack">
        <div class="card today-card">
          <div class="card-head">
            <span class="card-label">Today</span>
            <span class="card-cal">1,847 <span class="cal-unit">cal</span></span>
          </div>
          <div class="macro-row">
            <div class="macro-bar protein">
              <span class="bar-fill" style="width: 78%"></span>
              <span class="bar-label">Protein</span>
              <span class="bar-num">142g</span>
            </div>
            <div class="macro-bar carbs">
              <span class="bar-fill" style="width: 62%"></span>
              <span class="bar-label">Carbs</span>
              <span class="bar-num">186g</span>
            </div>
            <div class="macro-bar fat">
              <span class="bar-fill" style="width: 54%"></span>
              <span class="bar-label">Fat</span>
              <span class="bar-num">64g</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card describe-card">
          <div class="describe-prompt">"chicken caesar wrap and a coke"</div>
          <div class="describe-result">
            <div class="match">
              <span class="match-name">Chicken Caesar Wrap <span class="tier authoritative">Verified</span></span>
              <span class="match-cal">540 cal</span>
            </div>
            <div class="match">
              <span class="match-name">Coca-Cola, 12 fl oz <span class="tier authoritative">Verified</span></span>
              <span class="match-cal">140 cal</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pillars">
    <article class="pillar">
      <div class="pillar-icon">🎙</div>
      <h2>Speak it. Log it.</h2>
      <p>"I had a chicken caesar wrap with extra parmesan and a coke." Macroline parses natural language, finds the right foods, and logs the right portions. Voice or text, your call.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="pillar">
      <div class="pillar-icon">🔍</div>
      <h2>Honest data.</h2>
      <p>Every food links to its source — USDA, manufacturer pages, official restaurant nutrition. Tap any number to see where it came from. No more bad community entries with wrong macros.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="pillar">
      <div class="pillar-icon">🔌</div>
      <h2>Log from Claude. Or ChatGPT. Anywhere.</h2>
      <p>Macroline runs as an MCP server, so any modern AI assistant can log meals for you. Talk to Claude on your laptop, ChatGPT on your phone — it all lands in your diary.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="moat">
    <h2>Every number, sourced.</h2>
    <p class="moat-lede">
      Macroline is built on a different principle than most trackers: <strong>show your work.</strong>
      Every food row in our database carries a provenance tier and a citation URL.
    </p>
    <div class="tier-grid">
      <div class="tier authoritative">
        <span class="tier-dot"></span>
        <h3>Authoritative</h3>
        <p>USDA FoodData Central, manufacturer pages, official chain restaurant nutrition. The gold standard.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tier computed">
        <span class="tier-dot"></span>
        <h3>Computed</h3>
        <p>Recipe foods derived from authoritative ingredients with summed macros. Math is verifiable.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tier estimated">
        <span class="tier-dot"></span>
        <h3>Estimated</h3>
        <p>AI-researched from cross-checked sources when no official data exists. Cited and flagged.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tier unverified">
        <span class="tier-dot"></span>
        <h3>Unverified</h3>
        <p>User-submitted entries, awaiting community confirmation. Visible but never silently trusted.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Privacy promises strip — surfaces what's deep on /privacy. One of
       the strongest trust signals available; was hidden three clicks deep. -->
  <section class="promises">
    <p class="promises-label">Our promises</p>
    <div class="promises-grid">
      <article class="promise promise-protein">
        <span class="promise-icon" aria-hidden="true">🛡</span>
        <h3>Never sold</h3>
        <p>Your data isn't a product.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="promise promise-carbs">
        <span class="promise-icon" aria-hidden="true">🚫</span>
        <h3>Never trained</h3>
        <p>We don't feed your meals to AI models.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="promise promise-fat">
        <span class="promise-icon" aria-hidden="true">↗</span>
        <h3>Export anytime</h3>
        <p>CSV + JSON, your whole history.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="promise promise-accent">
        <span class="promise-icon" aria-hidden="true">🗑</span>
        <h3>Delete in one tap</h3>
        <p>Cascades through every record.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Founder note — the site had no human anywhere. This is the single
       highest-impact warmth fix for a category as personal as nutrition. -->
  <section class="founder">
    <div class="founder-photo">
      <img
        src="/founder.jpg"
        alt="Mike — Macroline founder"
        loading="lazy"
        width="220"
        height="280"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="founder-text">
      <h2>Built by one person who got tired of bad food data.</h2>
      <p>
        I'm Mike. I built Macroline because every macro tracker I tried lied to me — bad
        community entries, wrong serving sizes, "estimates" that were guesses. The whole
        product is one bet: if every number can be traced to a real source, people will trust it.
      </p>
      <p>
        If something's off, I read the support inbox personally. Email me anytime at
        <a href="mailto:info@macroline.app">info@macroline.app</a>.
      </p>
      <p class="founder-sig">— Mike, founder</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="download" class="download">
    <h2>Public TestFlight is open now.</h2>
    <p>App Store launch May 21. Drop your email below if you'd rather wait for the public release.</p>
    <a href="https://testflight.apple.com/join/SBhsGn9q" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="testflight-cta">
      Join TestFlight beta →
    </a>
    <p class="download-or">Or wait for App Store launch — drop your email:</p>
    <form class="signup-form waitlist-form" action="https://api.macroline.app/api/waitlist" method="post" data-source="home">
      <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="you@example.com" required />
      <button type="submit">Join waitlist</button>
      <p class="waitlist-msg" role="status" aria-live="polite"></p>
    </form>
    <p class="download-note">No spam. One launch email. Unsubscribe in one click.</p>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  /* Navy hero band — breaks out of the constrained <main> to fill the
     viewport, then re-constrains its inner content. Bridges the visual
     seam between marketing site (light) and the iOS app (navy) so the
     handoff at install feels continuous. */
  .hero {
    margin-inline: calc(50% - 50vw);
    padding-inline: max(24px, calc(50vw - 538px));
    padding-block: 80px 72px;
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse 700px 500px at 92% 8%, rgba(91, 158, 255, 0.22) 0%, transparent 55%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse 600px 450px at 4% 96%, rgba(139, 108, 255, 0.16) 0%, transparent 60%),
      linear-gradient(180deg, #0E1A35 0%, #0A1628 60%, #061029 100%);
    color: #F8FAFC;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.1fr 1fr;
    gap: 48px;
    align-items: center;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.12);
  }
  @media (max-width: 880px) {
    .hero { grid-template-columns: 1fr; padding-block: 56px 48px; }
    .hero-text { text-align: center; }
    .cta-row { justify-content: center; }
  }
  /* v1.5: hide the in-app preview cards on narrow viewports — at 390px
     wide the food entries shrink below readability and the phone mockup
     becomes visual filler, not product proof. */
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .hero-preview { display: none; }
  }
  .eyebrow {
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #5B9EFF;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
  }
  .hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(40px, 6.5vw, 72px);
    line-height: 1.02;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    margin: 0;
    color: #FFFFFF;
  }
  .hero-sub {
    font-size: 18px;
    color: #94B3D7;
    margin: 22px 0 0;
    max-width: 540px;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .cta-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-top: 28px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .btn-primary, .btn-ghost {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 14px 24px;
    border-radius: var(--r-pill);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 15px;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  /* Inside the navy hero band, the primary CTA flips to brand blue
     on near-black so it reads as a glowing pill against the gradient. */
  .hero .btn-primary {
    background: #5B9EFF;
    color: #04122E;
  }
  .hero .btn-primary:hover { background: #76B6FF; text-decoration: none; }
  .hero .btn-ghost {
    color: #F8FAFC;
    border: 1px solid rgba(248, 250, 252, 0.22);
  }
  .hero .btn-ghost:hover { background: rgba(248, 250, 252, 0.08); text-decoration: none; }
  .cta-sub { color: #8AA0C4; font-size: 13px; margin-top: 18px; max-width: 540px; line-height: 1.5; }

  /* Hero preview — stylized in-app card */
  .hero-preview {
    position: relative;
    min-height: 420px;
  }
  .card-stack {
    position: relative;
    height: 100%;
  }
  .card {
    background: linear-gradient(160deg, #1a2a4a 0%, #0f1830 100%);
    border: 1px solid rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.15);
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: 22px;
    color: #f8fafc;
    box-shadow: 0 30px 60px -20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4), 0 8px 16px -8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    backdrop-filter: blur(16px);
  }
  .today-card {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 360px;
    transform: rotate(-1.5deg);
    margin-left: auto;
  }
  .describe-card {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 320px;
    margin-top: -32px;
    margin-left: 0;
    transform: rotate(2deg);
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }
  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    .card {
      background: linear-gradient(160deg, #1a2a4a 0%, #0a0f1f 100%);
      border-color: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.2);
    }
  }
  .card-head {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: baseline;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }
  .card-label {
    font-size: 12px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: #94a3b8;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .card-cal {
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
  .cal-unit {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: #94a3b8;
    font-weight: 400;
    margin-left: 4px;
  }
  .macro-row { display: grid; gap: 10px; }
  .macro-bar {
    position: relative;
    height: 28px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 0 12px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    overflow: hidden;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .bar-fill {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0 auto 0 0;
    border-radius: 14px;
    opacity: 0.5;
  }
  .macro-bar.protein .bar-fill { background: var(--protein); }
  .macro-bar.carbs   .bar-fill { background: var(--carbs); }
  .macro-bar.fat     .bar-fill { background: var(--fat); }
  .bar-label, .bar-num { position: relative; z-index: 1; }
  .bar-num { font-family: ui-monospace, 'SF Mono', monospace; font-weight: 600; }

  .describe-prompt {
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: #94a3b8;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    padding: 10px 14px;
    background: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.1);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--primary);
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .describe-result { display: grid; gap: 10px; }
  .match {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 10px 12px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
    border-radius: 10px;
    font-size: 13px;
  }
  .match-name { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; }
  .match-cal { font-weight: 600; font-family: ui-monospace, 'SF Mono', monospace; font-size: 12px; }
  .tier {
    font-size: 9px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .tier.authoritative { background: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.2); color: #34d399; }

  .pillars {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: 20px;
    margin-top: 80px;
  }
  .pillar {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--r-lg);
    padding: 28px;
  }
  .pillar-icon { font-size: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .pillar h2 { font-size: 22px; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .pillar p { color: var(--text-muted); margin: 0; line-height: 1.6; }

  .moat {
    margin-top: 100px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .moat h2 { font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px); }
  .moat-lede { color: var(--text-muted); max-width: 600px; margin: 16px auto 40px; font-size: 17px; }
  .tier-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: 16px;
    text-align: left;
  }
  .tier-grid .tier {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--r-md);
    padding: 20px;
    font-size: inherit;
    text-transform: none;
    letter-spacing: normal;
    font-weight: normal;
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .tier-grid .tier h3 { font-size: 16px; margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .tier-grid .tier p { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-muted); margin: 0; }
  .tier-dot {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 10px;
    height: 10px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .tier-grid .authoritative .tier-dot { background: #10B981; }
  .tier-grid .computed     .tier-dot { background: #3B82F6; }
  .tier-grid .estimated    .tier-dot { background: #EAB308; }
  .tier-grid .unverified   .tier-dot { background: #94A3B8; }

  /* Privacy promises strip — surfaces the /privacy commitments. 4-up
     desktop / 2x2 tablet / 1-col mobile. Icon chips use the macro
     palette (protein/carbs/fat/accent) so it picks up the brand. */
  .promises {
    margin-top: 100px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .promises-label {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0 0 24px;
  }
  .promises-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 16px;
    text-align: left;
  }
  @media (max-width: 880px) {
    .promises-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  }
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .promises-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  .promise {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--r-md);
    padding: 20px;
  }
  .promise-icon {
    display: inline-grid;
    place-items: center;
    width: 36px;
    height: 36px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    font-size: 18px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .promise-protein .promise-icon { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--protein) 16%, transparent); }
  .promise-carbs   .promise-icon { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--carbs) 16%, transparent); }
  .promise-fat     .promise-icon { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--fat) 16%, transparent); }
  .promise-accent  .promise-icon { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 16%, transparent); }
  .promise h3 {
    font-size: 15px;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .promise p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Founder block — between provenance/promises and the download CTA.
     Rectangular 220x280 photo on desktop (not a circular avatar) +
     name + 60-100 word note. Photo stacks above the copy on mobile. */
  .founder {
    margin-top: 80px;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr;
    gap: 32px;
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--r-lg);
    padding: 32px;
    align-items: start;
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .founder { grid-template-columns: 1fr; text-align: center; }
    .founder-photo { justify-self: center; max-width: 280px; width: 100%; }
  }
  .founder-photo {
    position: relative;
  }
  .founder-photo img {
    width: 220px;
    height: 280px;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: var(--r-lg);
    display: block;
    /* Subtle macro-gradient outline so the photo edge picks up the
       brand palette without overpowering the lifestyle shot. */
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--protein) 30%, var(--border));
    box-shadow:
      0 0 0 1px color-mix(in srgb, var(--carbs) 12%, transparent),
      0 12px 28px -16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35);
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .founder-photo img { width: 100%; height: auto; aspect-ratio: 220 / 280; max-width: 280px; }
  }
  .founder-text h2 {
    font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 28px);
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .founder-text p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    font-size: 15px;
  }
  .founder-text .founder-sig {
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 14px;
    margin-top: 14px;
  }

  .download {
    margin-top: 80px;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 60px 24px;
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--r-lg);
  }
  .download h2 { font-size: 32px; }
  .download p { color: var(--text-muted); margin-top: 12px; }
  .download-note { font-size: 12px; margin-top: 14px; }
  .download-or {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 28px 0 10px;
  }
  .testflight-cta {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    margin-top: 24px;
    padding: 16px 32px;
    background: var(--primary);
    color: white;
    border: none;
    border-radius: var(--r-pill);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 16px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.15s ease;
  }
  .testflight-cta:hover { background: var(--primary-hover); color: white; text-decoration: none; }
  .signup-form {
    display: flex;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-top: 0;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .signup-form input {
    padding: 12px 16px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--r-pill);
    font-size: 15px;
    min-width: 240px;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .signup-form button {
    padding: 12px 20px;
    background: var(--primary);
    color: white;
    border: none;
    border-radius: var(--r-pill);
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
  }
</style>
